cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CC

The paper discusses the evaluation of information services, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The ISE Model proposed in the paper takes into account various dimensions that influence the adoption, use, impact, and diffusion of information services, which aligns with the interdisciplinary nature of the aforementioned sub-categories.
